						               													<description>&amp;quot;In the middle of the s. XV in Galiza several power struggles took place in different regions. The warring factions acted in order to gain sufficient influence to gain control of these regions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Marshal will move through the different regions and determine in which territory the revolt will take place while the 3 factions position their followers to stand in front.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Irmandinhos is a board game of political and military intrigue that takes place during the final period of the Second Irmandi&amp;ntilde;a Revolt (1469) in which three players will assume the role of different important characters and will have to make secret decisions for the three factions to make. Control each of the regions in play according to your character's goals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After completing the six rounds, the player with the most goals accomplished will be the winner.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players program actions in a hidden way through the intrigue cards, choosing the order in which they will be carried out to try to make a certain faction obtain a greater presence in the territory where the battle takes place. These territories will vary during the game. The player who manages to meet the requirements set by his character card before the 6 rounds will be the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
